.It Va folder-hook-FULLNAME
When a folder named `FULLNAME' is opened,
the macro corresponding to the value of this variable is executed.
Unlike other folder specifications,
the fully expanded name of a folder, without metacharacters,
is used to avoid ambiguities.
However, if the mailbox resides under
.Va folder
then the usual `+' specification is tried in addition, e.g., if
.Va folder
is `mail' (and thus relative to the user's home directory) then
.Pa /home/usr1/mail/sent
will be tried as `folder-hook-/home/usr1/mail/sent' first, but then
followed by `folder-hook-+sent'.
